rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0001
rows.name:
Have I told you about how I've
traveled all over Alst as a botanist?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0002
rows.name: Let me give you a few tips.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0003
rows.name: What would you like to know?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0008
rows.name: Ever hear of the Sirius Anemone?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0009
rows.name:
You don't see many around too often,
but you can usually find them down in
the Fons Maim Waters.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0010
rows.name: Well? Did I help, or did I help?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0011
rows.name: Have you heard of the Amber Leaf?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0012
rows.name:
It's rare finding any kind of plant life
in Superbia due to its aridity, but I
found some in the Old City of Teddim.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0013
rows.name: Well? Did I help, or did I help?

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0015
rows.name:
Never thought you'd be asking
me about that place...

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0016
rows.name: I'm afraid I can't help you there, mate.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0017
rows.name:
Luxuria's a closed-off country and
seldom few are allowed in.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0018
rows.name:
Plus you never know where the Divine Beast's
going to be from one day to the next!

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0019
rows.name:
Heh, I guess I'm not done with my
research just yet!
